801
802void
803ngx_http_handler(ngx_http_request_t *r)
804{
805 ngx_http_core_main_conf_t *cmcf;
806
807 r->connection->log->action = NULL;
808
809 if (!r->internal) {
810 switch (r->headers_in.connection_type) {
811 case 0:
812 r->keepalive = (r->http_version > NGX_HTTP_VERSION_10);
813 break;
814
815 case NGX_HTTP_CONNECTION_CLOSE:
816 r->keepalive = 0;
817 break;
818
819 case NGX_HTTP_CONNECTION_KEEP_ALIVE:
820 r->keepalive = 1;
821 break;
822 }
823
824 r->lingering_close = (r->headers_in.content_length_n > 0
825 || r->headers_in.chunked);
826 r->phase_handler = 0;
827
828 } else {
829 cmcf = ngx_http_get_module_main_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
830 r->phase_handler = cmcf->phase_engine.server_rewrite_index;
831 }
832
833 r->valid_location = 1;
834#if (NGX_HTTP_GZIP)
835 r->gzip_tested = 0;
836 r->gzip_ok = 0;
837 r->gzip_vary = 0;
838#endif
839
840 r->write_event_handler = ngx_http_core_run_phases;
841 ngx_http_core_run_phases(r);
842}
843
844
845void
846ngx_http_core_run_phases(ngx_http_request_t *r)
847{
848 ngx_int_t rc;
849 ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph;
850 ngx_http_core_main_conf_t *cmcf;
851
852 cmcf = ngx_http_get_module_main_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
853
854 ph = cmcf->phase_engine.handlers;
855
856 while (ph[r->phase_handler].checker) {
857
858 rc = ph[r->phase_handler].checker(r, &ph[r->phase_handler]);
859
860 if (rc == NGX_OK) {
861 return;
862 }
863 }
864}
865
866
867ngx_int_t
868ngx_http_core_generic_phase(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph)
869{
870 ngx_int_t rc;
871
872 /*
873 * generic phase checker,
874 * used by the post read and pre-access phases
875 */
876
877 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
878 "generic phase: %ui", r->phase_handler);
879
880 rc = ph->handler(r);
881
882 if (rc == NGX_OK) {
883 r->phase_handler = ph->next;
884 return NGX_AGAIN;
885 }
886
887 if (rc == NGX_DECLINED) {
888 r->phase_handler++;
889 return NGX_AGAIN;
890 }
891
892 if (rc == NGX_AGAIN || rc == NGX_DONE) {
893 return NGX_OK;
894 }
895
896 /* rc == NGX_ERROR || rc == NGX_HTTP_... */
897
898 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, rc);
899
900 return NGX_OK;
901}
902
903
904ngx_int_t
905ngx_http_core_rewrite_phase(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph)
906{
907 ngx_int_t rc;
908
909 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
910 "rewrite phase: %ui", r->phase_handler);
911
912 rc = ph->handler(r);
913
914 if (rc == NGX_DECLINED) {
915 r->phase_handler++;
916 return NGX_AGAIN;
917 }
918
919 if (rc == NGX_DONE) {
920 return NGX_OK;
921 }
922
923 /* NGX_OK, NGX_AGAIN, NGX_ERROR, NGX_HTTP_... */
924
925 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, rc);
926
927 return NGX_OK;
928}

930
931ngx_int_t
932ngx_http_core_find_config_phase(ngx_http_request_t *r,
933 ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph)
934{
935 u_char *p;
936 size_t len;
937 ngx_int_t rc;
938 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
939
940 r->content_handler = NULL;
941 r->uri_changed = 0;
942
943 rc = ngx_http_core_find_location(r);
944
945 if (rc == NGX_ERROR) {
946 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
947 return NGX_OK;
948 }
949
950 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
951
952 if (!r->internal && clcf->internal) {
953 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_NOT_FOUND);
954 return NGX_OK;
955 }
956
957 ngx_log_debug2(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
958 "using configuration \"%s%V\"",
959 (clcf->noname ? "*" : (clcf->exact_match ? "=" : "")),
960 &clcf->name);
961
962 ngx_http_update_location_config(r);
963
964 ngx_log_debug2(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
965 "http cl:%O max:%O",
966 r->headers_in.content_length_n, clcf->client_max_body_size);
967
968 if (r->headers_in.content_length_n != -1
969 && !r->discard_body
970 && clcf->client_max_body_size
971 && clcf->client_max_body_size < r->headers_in.content_length_n)
972 {
973 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0,
974 "client intended to send too large body: %O bytes",
975 r->headers_in.content_length_n);
976
977 r->expect_tested = 1;
978 (void) ngx_http_discard_request_body(r);
979 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE);
980 return NGX_OK;
981 }
982
983 if (rc == NGX_DONE) {
984 ngx_http_clear_location(r);
985
986 r->headers_out.location = ngx_list_push(&r->headers_out.headers);
987 if (r->headers_out.location == NULL) {
988 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
989 return NGX_OK;
990 }
991
992 r->headers_out.location->hash = 1;
993 ngx_str_set(&r->headers_out.location->key, "Location");
994
995 if (r->args.len == 0) {
996 r->headers_out.location->value = clcf->name;
997
998 } else {
999 len = clcf->name.len + 1 + r->args.len;
1000 p = ngx_pnalloc(r->pool, len);
1001
1002 if (p == NULL) {
1003 ngx_http_clear_location(r);
1004 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
1005 return NGX_OK;
1006 }
1007
1008 r->headers_out.location->value.len = len;
1009 r->headers_out.location->value.data = p;
1010
1011 p = ngx_cpymem(p, clcf->name.data, clcf->name.len);
1012 *p++ = '?';
1013 ngx_memcpy(p, r->args.data, r->args.len);
1014 }
1015
1016 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_MOVED_PERMANENTLY);
1017 return NGX_OK;
1018 }
1019
1020 r->phase_handler++;
1021 return NGX_AGAIN;
1022}
1023
1024
1025ngx_int_t
1026ngx_http_core_post_rewrite_phase(ngx_http_request_t *r,
1027 ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph)
1028{
1029 ngx_http_core_srv_conf_t *cscf;
1030
1031 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
1032 "post rewrite phase: %ui", r->phase_handler);
1033
1034 if (!r->uri_changed) {
1035 r->phase_handler++;
1036 return NGX_AGAIN;
1037 }
1038
1039 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
1040 "uri changes: %d", r->uri_changes);
1041
1042 /*
1043 * gcc before 3.3 compiles the broken code for
1044 * if (r->uri_changes-- == 0)
1045 * if the r->uri_changes is defined as
1046 * unsigned uri_changes:4
1047 */
1048
1049 r->uri_changes--;
1050
1051 if (r->uri_changes == 0) {
1052 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0,
1053 "rewrite or internal redirection cycle "
1054 "while processing \"%V\"", &r->uri);
1055
1056 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
1057 return NGX_OK;
1058 }
1059
1060 r->phase_handler = ph->next;
1061
1062 cscf = ngx_http_get_module_srv_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1063 r->loc_conf = cscf->ctx->loc_conf;
1064
1065 return NGX_AGAIN;
1066}
1067
1068
1069ngx_int_t
1070ngx_http_core_access_phase(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph)
1071{
1072 ngx_int_t rc;
1073 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
1074
1075 if (r != r->main) {
1076 r->phase_handler = ph->next;
1077 return NGX_AGAIN;
1078 }
1079
1080 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
1081 "access phase: %ui", r->phase_handler);
1082
1083 rc = ph->handler(r);
1084
1085 if (rc == NGX_DECLINED) {
1086 r->phase_handler++;
1087 return NGX_AGAIN;
1088 }
1089
1090 if (rc == NGX_AGAIN || rc == NGX_DONE) {
1091 return NGX_OK;
1092 }
1093
1094 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1095
1096 if (clcf->satisfy == NGX_HTTP_SATISFY_ALL) {
1097
1098 if (rc == NGX_OK) {
1099 r->phase_handler++;
1100 return NGX_AGAIN;
1101 }
1102
1103 } else {
1104 if (rc == NGX_OK) {
1105 r->access_code = 0;
1106
1107 if (r->headers_out.www_authenticate) {
1108 r->headers_out.www_authenticate->hash = 0;
1109 }
1110
1111 r->phase_handler = ph->next;
1112 return NGX_AGAIN;
1113 }
1114
1115 if (rc == NGX_HTTP_FORBIDDEN || rc == NGX_HTTP_UNAUTHORIZED) {
1116 if (r->access_code != NGX_HTTP_UNAUTHORIZED) {
1117 r->access_code = rc;
1118 }
1119
1120 r->phase_handler++;
1121 return NGX_AGAIN;
1122 }
1123 }
1124
1125 /* rc == NGX_ERROR || rc == NGX_HTTP_... */
1126
1127 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, rc);
1128 return NGX_OK;
1129}
1130
1131
1132ngx_int_t
1133ngx_http_core_post_access_phase(ngx_http_request_t *r,
1134 ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph)
1135{
1136 ngx_int_t access_code;
1137
1138 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
1139 "post access phase: %ui", r->phase_handler);
1140
1141 access_code = r->access_code;
1142
1143 if (access_code) {
1144 if (access_code == NGX_HTTP_FORBIDDEN) {
1145 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0,
1146 "access forbidden by rule");
1147 }
1148
1149 r->access_code = 0;
1150 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, access_code);
1151 return NGX_OK;
1152 }
1153
1154 r->phase_handler++;
1155 return NGX_AGAIN;
1156}
1157
1158
1159ngx_int_t
1160ngx_http_core_content_phase(ngx_http_request_t *r,
1161 ngx_http_phase_handler_t *ph)
1162{
1163 size_t root;
1164 ngx_int_t rc;
1165 ngx_str_t path;
1166
1167 if (r->content_handler) {
1168 r->write_event_handler = ngx_http_request_empty_handler;
1169 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, r->content_handler(r));
1170 return NGX_OK;
1171 }
1172
1173 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
1174 "content phase: %ui", r->phase_handler);
1175
1176 rc = ph->handler(r);
1177
1178 if (rc != NGX_DECLINED) {
1179 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, rc);
1180 return NGX_OK;
1181 }
1182
1183 /* rc == NGX_DECLINED */
1184
1185 ph++;
1186
1187 if (ph->checker) {
1188 r->phase_handler++;
1189 return NGX_AGAIN;
1190 }
1191
1192 /* no content handler was found */
1193
1194 if (r->uri.data[r->uri.len - 1] == '/') {
1195
1196 if (ngx_http_map_uri_to_path(r, &path, &root, 0) != NULL) {
1197 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0,
1198 "directory index of \"%s\" is forbidden", path.data);
1199 }
1200
1201 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_FORBIDDEN);
1202 return NGX_OK;
1203 }
1204
1205 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0, "no handler found");
1206
1207 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_NOT_FOUND);
1208 return NGX_OK;
1209}

1211
1212void
1213ngx_http_update_location_config(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1214{
1215 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
1216
1217 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1218
1219 if (r->method & clcf->limit_except) {
1220 r->loc_conf = clcf->limit_except_loc_conf;
1221 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1222 }
1223
1224 if (r == r->main) {
1225 ngx_set_connection_log(r->connection, clcf->error_log);
1226 }
1227
1228 if ((ngx_io.flags & NGX_IO_SENDFILE) && clcf->sendfile) {
1229 r->connection->sendfile = 1;
1230
1231 } else {
1232 r->connection->sendfile = 0;
1233 }
1234
1235 if (clcf->client_body_in_file_only) {
1236 r->request_body_in_file_only = 1;
1237 r->request_body_in_persistent_file = 1;
1238 r->request_body_in_clean_file =
1239 clcf->client_body_in_file_only == NGX_HTTP_REQUEST_BODY_FILE_CLEAN;
1240 r->request_body_file_log_level = NGX_LOG_NOTICE;
1241
1242 } else {
1243 r->request_body_file_log_level = NGX_LOG_WARN;
1244 }
1245
1246 r->request_body_in_single_buf = clcf->client_body_in_single_buffer;
1247
1248 if (r->keepalive) {
1249 if (clcf->keepalive_timeout == 0) {
1250 r->keepalive = 0;
1251
1252 } else if (r->connection->requests >= clcf->keepalive_requests) {
1253 r->keepalive = 0;
1254
1255 } else if (r->headers_in.msie6
1256 && r->method == NGX_HTTP_POST
1257 && (clcf->keepalive_disable
1258 & NGX_HTTP_KEEPALIVE_DISABLE_MSIE6))
1259 {
1260 /*
1261 * MSIE may wait for some time if an response for
1262 * a POST request was sent over a keepalive connection
1263 */
1264 r->keepalive = 0;
1265
1266 } else if (r->headers_in.safari
1267 && (clcf->keepalive_disable
1268 & NGX_HTTP_KEEPALIVE_DISABLE_SAFARI))
1269 {
1270 /*
1271 * Safari may send a POST request to a closed keepalive
1272 * connection and may stall for some time, see
1273 * https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=5760
1274 */
1275 r->keepalive = 0;
1276 }
1277 }
1278
1279 if (!clcf->tcp_nopush) {
1280 /* disable TCP_NOPUSH/TCP_CORK use */
1281 r->connection->tcp_nopush = NGX_TCP_NOPUSH_DISABLED;
1282 }
1283
1284 if (r->limit_rate == 0) {
1285 r->limit_rate = clcf->limit_rate;
1286 }
1287
1288 if (clcf->handler) {
1289 r->content_handler = clcf->handler;
1290 }
1291}

1293
1294/*
1295 * NGX_OK - exact or regex match
1296 * NGX_DONE - auto redirect
1297 * NGX_AGAIN - inclusive match
1298 * NGX_ERROR - regex error
1299 * NGX_DECLINED - no match
1300 */
1301
1302static ngx_int_t
1303ngx_http_core_find_location(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1304{
1305 ngx_int_t rc;
1306 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *pclcf;
1307#if (NGX_PCRE)
1308 ngx_int_t n;
1309 ngx_uint_t noregex;
1310 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf, **clcfp;
1311
1312 noregex = 0;
1313#endif
1314
1315 pclcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1316
1317 rc = ngx_http_core_find_static_location(r, pclcf->static_locations);
1318
1319 if (rc == NGX_AGAIN) {
1320
1321#if (NGX_PCRE)
1322 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1323
1324 noregex = clcf->noregex;
1325#endif
1326
1327 /* look up nested locations */
1328
1329 rc = ngx_http_core_find_location(r);
1330 }
1331
1332 if (rc == NGX_OK || rc == NGX_DONE) {
1333 return rc;
1334 }
1335
1336 /* rc == NGX_DECLINED or rc == NGX_AGAIN in nested location */
1337
1338#if (NGX_PCRE)
1339
1340 if (noregex == 0 && pclcf->regex_locations) {
1341
1342 for (clcfp = pclcf->regex_locations; *clcfp; clcfp++) {
1343
1344 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
1345 "test location: ~ \"%V\"", &(*clcfp)->name);
1346
1347 n = ngx_http_regex_exec(r, (*clcfp)->regex, &r->uri);
1348
1349 if (n == NGX_OK) {
1350 r->loc_conf = (*clcfp)->loc_conf;
1351
1352 /* look up nested locations */
1353
1354 rc = ngx_http_core_find_location(r);
1355
1356 return (rc == NGX_ERROR) ? rc : NGX_OK;
1357 }
1358
1359 if (n == NGX_DECLINED) {
1360 continue;
1361 }
1362
1363 return NGX_ERROR;
1364 }
1365 }
1366#endif
1367
1368 return rc;
1369}
1370
1371
1372/*
1373 * NGX_OK - exact match
1374 * NGX_DONE - auto redirect
1375 * NGX_AGAIN - inclusive match
1376 * NGX_DECLINED - no match
1377 */
1378
1379static ngx_int_t
1380ngx_http_core_find_static_location(ngx_http_request_t *r,
1381 ngx_http_location_tree_node_t *node)
1382{
1383 u_char *uri;
1384 size_t len, n;
1385 ngx_int_t rc, rv;
1386
1387 len = r->uri.len;
1388 uri = r->uri.data;
1389
1390 rv = NGX_DECLINED;
1391
1392 for ( ;; ) {
1393
1394 if (node == NULL) {
1395 return rv;
1396 }
1397
1398 ngx_log_debug2(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
1399 "test location: \"%*s\"",
1400 (size_t) node->len, node->name);
1401
1402 n = (len <= (size_t) node->len) ? len : node->len;
1403
1404 rc = ngx_filename_cmp(uri, node->name, n);
1405
1406 if (rc != 0) {
1407 node = (rc < 0) ? node->left : node->right;
1408
1409 continue;
1410 }
1411
1412 if (len > (size_t) node->len) {
1413
1414 if (node->inclusive) {
1415
1416 r->loc_conf = node->inclusive->loc_conf;
1417 rv = NGX_AGAIN;
1418
1419 node = node->tree;
1420 uri += n;
1421 len -= n;
1422
1423 continue;
1424 }
1425
1426 /* exact only */
1427
1428 node = node->right;
1429
1430 continue;
1431 }
1432
1433 if (len == (size_t) node->len) {
1434
1435 if (node->exact) {
1436 r->loc_conf = node->exact->loc_conf;
1437 return NGX_OK;
1438
1439 } else {
1440 r->loc_conf = node->inclusive->loc_conf;
1441 return NGX_AGAIN;
1442 }
1443 }
1444
1445 /* len < node->len */
1446
1447 if (len + 1 == (size_t) node->len && node->auto_redirect) {
1448
1449 r->loc_conf = (node->exact) ? node->exact->loc_conf:
1450 node->inclusive->loc_conf;
1451 rv = NGX_DONE;
1452 }
1453
1454 node = node->left;
1455 }
1456}

1458
1459void *
1460ngx_http_test_content_type(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_hash_t *types_hash)
1461{
1462 u_char c, *lowcase;
1463 size_t len;
1464 ngx_uint_t i, hash;
1465
1466 if (types_hash->size == 0) {
1467 return (void *) 4;
1468 }
1469
1470 if (r->headers_out.content_type.len == 0) {
1471 return NULL;
1472 }
1473
1474 len = r->headers_out.content_type_len;
1475
1476 if (r->headers_out.content_type_lowcase == NULL) {
1477
1478 lowcase = ngx_pnalloc(r->pool, len);
1479 if (lowcase == NULL) {
1480 return NULL;
1481 }
1482
1483 r->headers_out.content_type_lowcase = lowcase;
1484
1485 hash = 0;
1486
1487 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
1488 c = ngx_tolower(r->headers_out.content_type.data[i]);
1489 hash = ngx_hash(hash, c);
1490 lowcase[i] = c;
1491 }
1492
1493 r->headers_out.content_type_hash = hash;
1494 }
1495
1496 return ngx_hash_find(types_hash, r->headers_out.content_type_hash,
1497 r->headers_out.content_type_lowcase, len);
1498}

1500
1501ngx_int_t
1502ngx_http_set_content_type(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1503{
1504 u_char c, *exten;
1505 ngx_str_t *type;
1506 ngx_uint_t i, hash;
1507 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
1508
1509 if (r->headers_out.content_type.len) {
1510 return NGX_OK;
1511 }
1512
1513 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1514
1515 if (r->exten.len) {
1516
1517 hash = 0;
1518
1519 for (i = 0; i < r->exten.len; i++) {
1520 c = r->exten.data[i];
1521
1522 if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') {
1523
1524 exten = ngx_pnalloc(r->pool, r->exten.len);
1525 if (exten == NULL) {
1526 return NGX_ERROR;
1527 }
1528
1529 hash = ngx_hash_strlow(exten, r->exten.data, r->exten.len);
1530
1531 r->exten.data = exten;
1532
1533 break;
1534 }
1535
1536 hash = ngx_hash(hash, c);
1537 }
1538
1539 type = ngx_hash_find(&clcf->types_hash, hash,
1540 r->exten.data, r->exten.len);
1541
1542 if (type) {
1543 r->headers_out.content_type_len = type->len;
1544 r->headers_out.content_type = *type;
1545
1546 return NGX_OK;
1547 }
1548 }
1549
1550 r->headers_out.content_type_len = clcf->default_type.len;
1551 r->headers_out.content_type = clcf->default_type;
1552
1553 return NGX_OK;
1554}

1556
1557void
1558ngx_http_set_exten(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1559{
1560 ngx_int_t i;
1561
1562 ngx_str_null(&r->exten);
1563
1564 for (i = r->uri.len - 1; i > 1; i--) {
1565 if (r->uri.data[i] == '.' && r->uri.data[i - 1] != '/') {
1566
1567 r->exten.len = r->uri.len - i - 1;
1568 r->exten.data = &r->uri.data[i + 1];
1569
1570 return;
1571
1572 } else if (r->uri.data[i] == '/') {
1573 return;
1574 }
1575 }
1576
1577 return;
1578}

1580
1581ngx_int_t
1582ngx_http_set_etag(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1583{
1584 ngx_table_elt_t *etag;
1585 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
1586
1587 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1588
1589 if (!clcf->etag) {
1590 return NGX_OK;
1591 }
1592
1593 etag = ngx_list_push(&r->headers_out.headers);
1594 if (etag == NULL) {
1595 return NGX_ERROR;
1596 }
1597
1598 etag->hash = 1;
1599 ngx_str_set(&etag->key, "ETag");
1600
1601 etag->value.data = ngx_pnalloc(r->pool, NGX_OFF_T_LEN + NGX_TIME_T_LEN + 3);
1602 if (etag->value.data == NULL) {
1603 etag->hash = 0;
1604 return NGX_ERROR;
1605 }
1606
1607 etag->value.len = ngx_sprintf(etag->value.data, "\"%xT-%xO\"",
1608 r->headers_out.last_modified_time,
1609 r->headers_out.content_length_n)
1610 - etag->value.data;
1611
1612 r->headers_out.etag = etag;
1613
1614 return NGX_OK;
1615}
1616
1617
1618void
1619ngx_http_weak_etag(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1620{
1621 size_t len;
1622 u_char *p;
1623 ngx_table_elt_t *etag;
1624
1625 etag = r->headers_out.etag;
1626
1627 if (etag == NULL) {
1628 return;
1629 }
1630
1631 if (etag->value.len > 2
1632 && etag->value.data[0] == 'W'
1633 && etag->value.data[1] == '/')
1634 {
1635 return;
1636 }
1637
1638 if (etag->value.len < 1 || etag->value.data[0] != '"') {
1639 r->headers_out.etag->hash = 0;
1640 r->headers_out.etag = NULL;
1641 return;
1642 }
1643
1644 p = ngx_pnalloc(r->pool, etag->value.len + 2);
1645 if (p == NULL) {
1646 r->headers_out.etag->hash = 0;
1647 r->headers_out.etag = NULL;
1648 return;
1649 }
1650
1651 len = ngx_sprintf(p, "W/%V", &etag->value) - p;
1652
1653 etag->value.data = p;
1654 etag->value.len = len;
1655}

1657
1658ngx_int_t
1659ngx_http_send_response(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_uint_t status,
1660 ngx_str_t *ct, ngx_http_complex_value_t *cv)
1661{
1662 ngx_int_t rc;
1663 ngx_str_t val;
1664 ngx_buf_t *b;
1665 ngx_chain_t out;
1666
1667 if (ngx_http_discard_request_body(r) != NGX_OK) {
1668 return NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;
1669 }
1670
1671 r->headers_out.status = status;
1672
1673 if (ngx_http_complex_value(r, cv, &val) != NGX_OK) {
1674 return NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;
1675 }
1676
1677 if (status == NGX_HTTP_MOVED_PERMANENTLY
1678 || status == NGX_HTTP_MOVED_TEMPORARILY
1679 || status == NGX_HTTP_SEE_OTHER
1680 || status == NGX_HTTP_TEMPORARY_REDIRECT
1681 || status == NGX_HTTP_PERMANENT_REDIRECT)
1682 {
1683 ngx_http_clear_location(r);
1684
1685 r->headers_out.location = ngx_list_push(&r->headers_out.headers);
1686 if (r->headers_out.location == NULL) {
1687 return NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;
1688 }
1689
1690 r->headers_out.location->hash = 1;
1691 ngx_str_set(&r->headers_out.location->key, "Location");
1692 r->headers_out.location->value = val;
1693
1694 return status;
1695 }
1696
1697 r->headers_out.content_length_n = val.len;
1698
1699 if (ct) {
1700 r->headers_out.content_type_len = ct->len;
1701 r->headers_out.content_type = *ct;
1702
1703 } else {
1704 if (ngx_http_set_content_type(r) != NGX_OK) {
1705 return NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;
1706 }
1707 }
1708
1709 if (r->method == NGX_HTTP_HEAD || (r != r->main && val.len == 0)) {
1710 return ngx_http_send_header(r);
1711 }
1712
1713 b = ngx_calloc_buf(r->pool);
1714 if (b == NULL) {
1715 return NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR;
1716 }
1717
1718 b->pos = val.data;
1719 b->last = val.data + val.len;
1720 b->memory = val.len ? 1 : 0;
1721 b->last_buf = (r == r->main) ? 1 : 0;
1722 b->last_in_chain = 1;
1723
1724 out.buf = b;
1725 out.next = NULL;
1726
1727 rc = ngx_http_send_header(r);
1728
1729 if (rc == NGX_ERROR || rc > NGX_OK || r->header_only) {
1730 return rc;
1731 }
1732
1733 return ngx_http_output_filter(r, &out);
1734}
1735
1736
1737ngx_int_t
1738ngx_http_send_header(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1739{
1740 if (r->post_action) {
1741 return NGX_OK;
1742 }
1743
1744 if (r->header_sent) {
1745 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ALERT, r->connection->log, 0,
1746 "header already sent");
1747 return NGX_ERROR;
1748 }
1749
1750 if (r->err_status) {
1751 r->headers_out.status = r->err_status;
1752 r->headers_out.status_line.len = 0;
1753 }
1754
1755 return ngx_http_top_header_filter(r);
1756}
1757
1758
1759ngx_int_t
1760ngx_http_output_filter(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_chain_t *in)
1761{
1762 ngx_int_t rc;
1763 ngx_connection_t *c;
1764
1765 c = r->connection;
1766
1767 ngx_log_debug2(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, c->log, 0,
1768 "http output filter \"%V?%V\"", &r->uri, &r->args);
1769
1770 rc = ngx_http_top_body_filter(r, in);
1771
1772 if (rc == NGX_ERROR) {
1773 /* NGX_ERROR may be returned by any filter */
1774 c->error = 1;
1775 }
1776
1777 return rc;
1778}

1780
1781u_char *
1782ngx_http_map_uri_to_path(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_str_t *path,
1783 size_t *root_length, size_t reserved)
1784{
1785 u_char *last;
1786 size_t alias;
1787 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
1788
1789 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1790
1791 alias = clcf->alias;
1792
1793 if (alias && !r->valid_location) {
1794 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ALERT, r->connection->log, 0,
1795 "\"alias\" cannot be used in location \"%V\" "
1796 "where URI was rewritten", &clcf->name);
1797 return NULL;
1798 }
1799
1800 if (clcf->root_lengths == NULL) {
1801
1802 *root_length = clcf->root.len;
1803
1804 path->len = clcf->root.len + reserved + r->uri.len - alias + 1;
1805
1806 path->data = ngx_pnalloc(r->pool, path->len);
1807 if (path->data == NULL) {
1808 return NULL;
1809 }
1810
1811 last = ngx_copy(path->data, clcf->root.data, clcf->root.len);
1812
1813 } else {
1814
1815 if (alias == NGX_MAX_SIZE_T_VALUE) {
1816 reserved += r->add_uri_to_alias ? r->uri.len + 1 : 1;
1817
1818 } else {
1819 reserved += r->uri.len - alias + 1;
1820 }
1821
1822 if (ngx_http_script_run(r, path, clcf->root_lengths->elts, reserved,
1823 clcf->root_values->elts)
1824 == NULL)
1825 {
1826 return NULL;
1827 }
1828
1829 if (ngx_get_full_name(r->pool, (ngx_str_t *) &ngx_cycle->prefix, path)
1830 != NGX_OK)
1831 {
1832 return NULL;
1833 }
1834
1835 *root_length = path->len - reserved;
1836 last = path->data + *root_length;
1837
1838 if (alias == NGX_MAX_SIZE_T_VALUE) {
1839 if (!r->add_uri_to_alias) {
1840 *last = '\0';
1841 return last;
1842 }
1843
1844 alias = 0;
1845 }
1846 }
1847
1848 last = ngx_cpystrn(last, r->uri.data + alias, r->uri.len - alias + 1);
1849
1850 return last;
1851}
1852
1853
1854ngx_int_t
1855ngx_http_auth_basic_user(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1856{
1857 ngx_str_t auth, encoded;
1858 ngx_uint_t len;
1859
1860 if (r->headers_in.user.len == 0 && r->headers_in.user.data != NULL) {
1861 return NGX_DECLINED;
1862 }
1863
1864 if (r->headers_in.authorization == NULL) {
1865 r->headers_in.user.data = (u_char *) "";
1866 return NGX_DECLINED;
1867 }
1868
1869 encoded = r->headers_in.authorization->value;
1870
1871 if (encoded.len < sizeof("Basic ") - 1
1872 || ngx_strncasecmp(encoded.data, (u_char *) "Basic ",
1873 sizeof("Basic ") - 1)
1874 != 0)
1875 {
1876 r->headers_in.user.data = (u_char *) "";
1877 return NGX_DECLINED;
1878 }
1879
1880 encoded.len -= sizeof("Basic ") - 1;
1881 encoded.data += sizeof("Basic ") - 1;
1882
1883 while (encoded.len && encoded.data[0] == ' ') {
1884 encoded.len--;
1885 encoded.data++;
1886 }
1887
1888 if (encoded.len == 0) {
1889 r->headers_in.user.data = (u_char *) "";
1890 return NGX_DECLINED;
1891 }
1892
1893 auth.len = ngx_base64_decoded_length(encoded.len);
1894 auth.data = ngx_pnalloc(r->pool, auth.len + 1);
1895 if (auth.data == NULL) {
1896 return NGX_ERROR;
1897 }
1898
1899 if (ngx_decode_base64(&auth, &encoded) != NGX_OK) {
1900 r->headers_in.user.data = (u_char *) "";
1901 return NGX_DECLINED;
1902 }
1903
1904 auth.data[auth.len] = '\0';
1905
1906 for (len = 0; len < auth.len; len++) {
1907 if (auth.data[len] == ':') {
1908 break;
1909 }
1910 }
1911
1912 if (len == 0 || len == auth.len) {
1913 r->headers_in.user.data = (u_char *) "";
1914 return NGX_DECLINED;
1915 }
1916
1917 r->headers_in.user.len = len;
1918 r->headers_in.user.data = auth.data;
1919 r->headers_in.passwd.len = auth.len - len - 1;
1920 r->headers_in.passwd.data = &auth.data[len + 1];
1921
1922 return NGX_OK;
1923}

1926#if (NGX_HTTP_GZIP)
1927
1928ngx_int_t
1929ngx_http_gzip_ok(ngx_http_request_t *r)
1930{
1931 time_t date, expires;
1932 ngx_uint_t p;
1933 ngx_array_t *cc;
1934 ngx_table_elt_t *e, *d, *ae;
1935 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
1936
1937 r->gzip_tested = 1;
1938
1939 if (r != r->main) {
1940 return NGX_DECLINED;
1941 }
1942
1943 ae = r->headers_in.accept_encoding;
1944 if (ae == NULL) {
1945 return NGX_DECLINED;
1946 }
1947
1948 if (ae->value.len < sizeof("gzip") - 1) {
1949 return NGX_DECLINED;
1950 }
1951
1952 /*
1953 * test first for the most common case "gzip,...":
1954 * MSIE: "gzip, deflate"
1955 * Firefox: "gzip,deflate"
1956 * Chrome: "gzip,deflate,sdch"
1957 * Safari: "gzip, deflate"
1958 * Opera: "gzip, deflate"
1959 */
1960
1961 if (ngx_memcmp(ae->value.data, "gzip,", 5) != 0
1962 && ngx_http_gzip_accept_encoding(&ae->value) != NGX_OK)
1963 {
1964 return NGX_DECLINED;
1965 }
1966
1967 clcf = ngx_http_get_module_loc_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
1968
1969 if (r->headers_in.msie6 && clcf->gzip_disable_msie6) {
1970 return NGX_DECLINED;
1971 }
1972
1973 if (r->http_version < clcf->gzip_http_version) {
1974 return NGX_DECLINED;
1975 }
1976
1977 if (r->headers_in.via == NULL) {
1978 goto ok;
1979 }
1980
1981 p = clcf->gzip_proxied;
1982
1983 if (p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_OFF) {
1984 return NGX_DECLINED;
1985 }
1986
1987 if (p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_ANY) {
1988 goto ok;
1989 }
1990
1991 if (r->headers_in.authorization && (p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_AUTH)) {
1992 goto ok;
1993 }
1994
1995 e = r->headers_out.expires;
1996
1997 if (e) {
1998
1999 if (!(p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_EXPIRED)) {
2000 return NGX_DECLINED;
2001 }
2002
2003 expires = ngx_parse_http_time(e->value.data, e->value.len);
2004 if (expires == NGX_ERROR) {
2005 return NGX_DECLINED;
2006 }
2007
2008 d = r->headers_out.date;
2009
2010 if (d) {
2011 date = ngx_parse_http_time(d->value.data, d->value.len);
2012 if (date == NGX_ERROR) {
2013 return NGX_DECLINED;
2014 }
2015
2016 } else {
2017 date = ngx_time();
2018 }
2019
2020 if (expires < date) {
2021 goto ok;
2022 }
2023
2024 return NGX_DECLINED;
2025 }
2026
2027 cc = &r->headers_out.cache_control;
2028
2029 if (cc->elts) {
2030
2031 if ((p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_NO_CACHE)
2032 && ngx_http_parse_multi_header_lines(cc, &ngx_http_gzip_no_cache,
2033 NULL)
2034 >= 0)
2035 {
2036 goto ok;
2037 }
2038
2039 if ((p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_NO_STORE)
2040 && ngx_http_parse_multi_header_lines(cc, &ngx_http_gzip_no_store,
2041 NULL)
2042 >= 0)
2043 {
2044 goto ok;
2045 }
2046
2047 if ((p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_PRIVATE)
2048 && ngx_http_parse_multi_header_lines(cc, &ngx_http_gzip_private,
2049 NULL)
2050 >= 0)
2051 {
2052 goto ok;
2053 }
2054
2055 return NGX_DECLINED;
2056 }
2057
2058 if ((p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_NO_LM) && r->headers_out.last_modified) {
2059 return NGX_DECLINED;
2060 }
2061
2062 if ((p & NGX_HTTP_GZIP_PROXIED_NO_ETAG) && r->headers_out.etag) {
2063 return NGX_DECLINED;
2064 }
2065
2066ok:
2067
2068#if (NGX_PCRE)
2069
2070 if (clcf->gzip_disable && r->headers_in.user_agent) {
2071
2072 if (ngx_regex_exec_array(clcf->gzip_disable,
2073 &r->headers_in.user_agent->value,
2074 r->connection->log)
2075 != NGX_DECLINED)
2076 {
2077 return NGX_DECLINED;
2078 }
2079 }
2080
2081#endif
2082
2083 r->gzip_ok = 1;
2084
2085 return NGX_OK;
2086}

2088
2089/*
2090 * gzip is enabled for the following quantities:
2091 * "gzip; q=0.001" ... "gzip; q=1.000"
2092 * gzip is disabled for the following quantities:
2093 * "gzip; q=0" ... "gzip; q=0.000", and for any invalid cases
2094 */
2095
2096static ngx_int_t
2097ngx_http_gzip_accept_encoding(ngx_str_t *ae)
2098{
2099 u_char *p, *start, *last;
2100
2101 start = ae->data;
2102 last = start + ae->len;
2103
2104 for ( ;; ) {
2105 p = ngx_strcasestrn(start, "gzip", 4 - 1);
2106 if (p == NULL) {
2107 return NGX_DECLINED;
2108 }
2109
2110 if (p == start || (*(p - 1) == ',' || *(p - 1) == ' ')) {
2111 break;
2112 }
2113
2114 start = p + 4;
2115 }
2116
2117 p += 4;
2118
2119 while (p < last) {
2120 switch (*p++) {
2121 case ',':
2122 return NGX_OK;
2123 case ';':
2124 goto quantity;
2125 case ' ':
2126 continue;
2127 default:
2128 return NGX_DECLINED;
2129 }
2130 }
2131
2132 return NGX_OK;
2133
2134quantity:
2135
2136 while (p < last) {
2137 switch (*p++) {
2138 case 'q':
2139 case 'Q':
2140 goto equal;
2141 case ' ':
2142 continue;
2143 default:
2144 return NGX_DECLINED;
2145 }
2146 }
2147
2148 return NGX_OK;
2149
2150equal:
2151
2152 if (p + 2 > last || *p++ != '=') {
2153 return NGX_DECLINED;
2154 }
2155
2156 if (ngx_http_gzip_quantity(p, last) == 0) {
2157 return NGX_DECLINED;
2158 }
2159
2160 return NGX_OK;
2161}
2162
2163
2164static ngx_uint_t
2165ngx_http_gzip_quantity(u_char *p, u_char *last)
2166{
2167 u_char c;
2168 ngx_uint_t n, q;
2169
2170 c = *p++;
2171
2172 if (c != '0' && c != '1') {
2173 return 0;
2174 }
2175
2176 q = (c - '0') * 100;
2177
2178 if (p == last) {
2179 return q;
2180 }
2181
2182 c = *p++;
2183
2184 if (c == ',' || c == ' ') {
2185 return q;
2186 }
2187
2188 if (c != '.') {
2189 return 0;
2190 }
2191
2192 n = 0;
2193
2194 while (p < last) {
2195 c = *p++;
2196
2197 if (c == ',' || c == ' ') {
2198 break;
2199 }
2200
2201 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
2202 q += c - '0';
2203 n++;
2204 continue;
2205 }
2206
2207 return 0;
2208 }
2209
2210 if (q > 100 || n > 3) {
2211 return 0;
2212 }
2213
2214 return q;
2215}

2450ngx_int_t
2451ngx_http_named_location(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_str_t *name)
2452{
2453 ngx_http_core_srv_conf_t *cscf;
2454 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t **clcfp;
2455 ngx_http_core_main_conf_t *cmcf;
2456
2457 r->main->count++;
2458 r->uri_changes--;
2459
2460 if (r->uri_changes == 0) {
2461 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0,
2462 "rewrite or internal redirection cycle "
2463 "while redirect to named location \"%V\"", name);
2464
2465 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
2466 return NGX_DONE;
2467 }
2468
2469 if (r->uri.len == 0) {
2470 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0,
2471 "empty URI in redirect to named location \"%V\"", name);
2472
2473 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
2474 return NGX_DONE;
2475 }
2476
2477 cscf = ngx_http_get_module_srv_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
2478
2479 if (cscf->named_locations) {
2480
2481 for (clcfp = cscf->named_locations; *clcfp; clcfp++) {
2482
2483 ngx_log_debug1(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
2484 "test location: \"%V\"", &(*clcfp)->name);
2485
2486 if (name->len != (*clcfp)->name.len
2487 || ngx_strncmp(name->data, (*clcfp)->name.data, name->len) != 0)
2488 {
2489 continue;
2490 }
2491
2492 ngx_log_debug3(NGX_LOG_DEBUG_HTTP, r->connection->log, 0,
2493 "using location: %V \"%V?%V\"",
2494 name, &r->uri, &r->args);
2495
2496 r->internal = 1;
2497 r->content_handler = NULL;
2498 r->uri_changed = 0;
2499 r->loc_conf = (*clcfp)->loc_conf;
2500
2501 /* clear the modules contexts */
2502 ngx_memzero(r->ctx, sizeof(void *) * ngx_http_max_module);
2503
2504 ngx_http_update_location_config(r);
2505
2506 cmcf = ngx_http_get_module_main_conf(r, ngx_http_core_module);
2507
2508 r->phase_handler = cmcf->phase_engine.location_rewrite_index;
2509
2510 r->write_event_handler = ngx_http_core_run_phases;
2511 ngx_http_core_run_phases(r);
2512
2513 return NGX_DONE;
2514 }
2515 }
2516
2517 ngx_log_error(NGX_LOG_ERR, r->connection->log, 0,
2518 "could not find named location \"%V\"", name);
2519
2520 ngx_http_finalize_request(r, NGX_HTTP_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
2521
2522 return NGX_DONE;
2523}

2613 int recursive)
2614{
2615 ngx_int_t rc;
2616 ngx_uint_t i, found;
2617 ngx_table_elt_t **h;
2618
2619 if (headers == NULL) {
2620 return ngx_http_get_forwarded_addr_internal(r, addr, value->data,
2621 value->len, proxies,
2622 recursive);
2623 }
2624
2625 i = headers->nelts;
2626 h = headers->elts;
2627
2628 rc = NGX_DECLINED;
2629
2630 found = 0;
2631
2632 while (i-- > 0) {
2633 rc = ngx_http_get_forwarded_addr_internal(r, addr, h[i]->value.data,
2634 h[i]->value.len, proxies,
2635 recursive);
2636
2637 if (!recursive) {
2638 break;
2639 }
2640
2641 if (rc == NGX_DECLINED && found) {
2642 rc = NGX_DONE;
2643 break;
2644 }
2645
2646 if (rc != NGX_OK) {
2647 break;
2648 }
2649
2650 found = 1;
2651 }
2652
2653 return rc;
2654}
2655
2656
2657static ngx_int_t
2658ngx_http_get_forwarded_addr_internal(ngx_http_request_t *r, ngx_addr_t *addr,
2659 u_char *xff, size_t xfflen, ngx_array_t *proxies, int recursive)
2660{
2661 u_char *p;
2662 ngx_int_t rc;
2663 ngx_addr_t paddr;
2664
2665 if (ngx_cidr_match(addr->sockaddr, proxies) != NGX_OK) {
2666 return NGX_DECLINED;
2667 }
2668
2669 for (p = xff + xfflen - 1; p > xff; p--, xfflen--) {
2670 if (*p != ' ' && *p != ',') {
2671 break;
2672 }
2673 }
2674
2675 for ( /* void */ ; p > xff; p--) {
2676 if (*p == ' ' || *p == ',') {
2677 p++;
2678 break;
2679 }
2680 }
2681
2682 if (ngx_parse_addr_port(r->pool, &paddr, p, xfflen - (p - xff)) != NGX_OK) {
2683 return NGX_DECLINED;
2684 }
2685
2686 *addr = paddr;
2687
2688 if (recursive && p > xff) {
2689 rc = ngx_http_get_forwarded_addr_internal(r, addr, xff, p - 1 - xff,
2690 proxies, 1);
2691
2692 if (rc == NGX_DECLINED) {
2693 return NGX_DONE;
2694 }
2695
2696 /* rc == NGX_OK || rc == NGX_DONE */
2697 return rc;
2698 }
2699
2700 return NGX_OK;
2701}

2703
2704static char *
2705ngx_http_core_server(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *dummy)
2706{
2707 char *rv;
2708 void *mconf;
2709 ngx_uint_t i;
2710 ngx_conf_t pcf;
2711 ngx_http_module_t *module;
2712 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
2713 ngx_http_conf_ctx_t *ctx, *http_ctx;
2714 ngx_http_listen_opt_t lsopt;
2715 ngx_http_core_srv_conf_t *cscf, **cscfp;
2716 ngx_http_core_main_conf_t *cmcf;
2717
2718 ctx = ngx_pcalloc(cf->pool, sizeof(ngx_http_conf_ctx_t));
2719 if (ctx == NULL) {
2720 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2721 }
2722
2723 http_ctx = cf->ctx;
2724 ctx->main_conf = http_ctx->main_conf;
2725
2726 /* the server{}'s srv_conf */
2727
2728 ctx->srv_conf = ngx_pcalloc(cf->pool, sizeof(void *) * ngx_http_max_module);
2729 if (ctx->srv_conf == NULL) {
2730 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2731 }
2732
2733 /* the server{}'s loc_conf */
2734
2735 ctx->loc_conf = ngx_pcalloc(cf->pool, sizeof(void *) * ngx_http_max_module);
2736 if (ctx->loc_conf == NULL) {
2737 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2738 }
2739
2740 for (i = 0; cf->cycle->modules[i]; i++) {
2741 if (cf->cycle->modules[i]->type != NGX_HTTP_MODULE) {
2742 continue;
2743 }
2744
2745 module = cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx;
2746
2747 if (module->create_srv_conf) {
2748 mconf = module->create_srv_conf(cf);
2749 if (mconf == NULL) {
2750 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2751 }
2752
2753 ctx->srv_conf[cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx_index] = mconf;
2754 }
2755
2756 if (module->create_loc_conf) {
2757 mconf = module->create_loc_conf(cf);
2758 if (mconf == NULL) {
2759 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2760 }
2761
2762 ctx->loc_conf[cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx_index] = mconf;
2763 }
2764 }
2765
2766
2767 /* the server configuration context */
2768
2769 cscf = ctx->srv_conf[ngx_http_core_module.ctx_index];
2770 cscf->ctx = ctx;
2771
2772
2773 cmcf = ctx->main_conf[ngx_http_core_module.ctx_index];
2774
2775 cscfp = ngx_array_push(&cmcf->servers);
2776 if (cscfp == NULL) {
2777 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2778 }
2779
2780 *cscfp = cscf;
2781
2782
2783 /* parse inside server{} */
2784
2785 pcf = *cf;
2786 cf->ctx = ctx;
2787 cf->cmd_type = NGX_HTTP_SRV_CONF;
2788
2789 rv = ngx_conf_parse(cf, NULL);
2790
2791 *cf = pcf;
2792
2793 if (rv == NGX_CONF_OK && !cscf->listen) {
2794 ngx_memzero(&lsopt, sizeof(ngx_http_listen_opt_t));
2795
2796 sin = &lsopt.sockaddr.sockaddr_in;
2797
2798 sin->sin_family = AF_INET;
2799#if (NGX_WIN32)
2800 sin->sin_port = htons(80);
2801#else
2802 sin->sin_port = htons((getuid() == 0) ? 80 : 8000);
2803#endif
2804 sin->sin_addr.s_addr = INADDR_ANY;
2805
2806 lsopt.socklen = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
2807
2808 lsopt.backlog = NGX_LISTEN_BACKLOG;
2809 lsopt.rcvbuf = -1;
2810 lsopt.sndbuf = -1;
2811#if (NGX_HAVE_SETFIB)
2812 lsopt.setfib = -1;
2813#endif
2814#if (NGX_HAVE_TCP_FASTOPEN)
2815 lsopt.fastopen = -1;
2816#endif
2817 lsopt.wildcard = 1;
2818
2819 (void) ngx_sock_ntop(&lsopt.sockaddr.sockaddr, lsopt.socklen,
2820 lsopt.addr, NGX_SOCKADDR_STRLEN, 1);
2821
2822 if (ngx_http_add_listen(cf, cscf, &lsopt) != NGX_OK) {
2823 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2824 }
2825 }
2826
2827 return rv;
2828}

2830
2831static char *
2832ngx_http_core_location(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *dummy)
2833{
2834 char *rv;
2835 u_char *mod;
2836 size_t len;
2837 ngx_str_t *value, *name;
2838 ngx_uint_t i;
2839 ngx_conf_t save;
2840 ngx_http_module_t *module;
2841 ngx_http_conf_ctx_t *ctx, *pctx;
2842 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf, *pclcf;
2843
2844 ctx = ngx_pcalloc(cf->pool, sizeof(ngx_http_conf_ctx_t));
2845 if (ctx == NULL) {
2846 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2847 }
2848
2849 pctx = cf->ctx;
2850 ctx->main_conf = pctx->main_conf;
2851 ctx->srv_conf = pctx->srv_conf;
2852
2853 ctx->loc_conf = ngx_pcalloc(cf->pool, sizeof(void *) * ngx_http_max_module);
2854 if (ctx->loc_conf == NULL) {
2855 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2856 }
2857
2858 for (i = 0; cf->cycle->modules[i]; i++) {
2859 if (cf->cycle->modules[i]->type != NGX_HTTP_MODULE) {
2860 continue;
2861 }
2862
2863 module = cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx;
2864
2865 if (module->create_loc_conf) {
2866 ctx->loc_conf[cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx_index] =
2867 module->create_loc_conf(cf);
2868 if (ctx->loc_conf[cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx_index] == NULL) {
2869 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2870 }
2871 }
2872 }
2873
2874 clcf = ctx->loc_conf[ngx_http_core_module.ctx_index];
2875 clcf->loc_conf = ctx->loc_conf;
2876
2877 value = cf->args->elts;
2878
2879 if (cf->args->nelts == 3) {
2880
2881 len = value[1].len;
2882 mod = value[1].data;
2883 name = &value[2];
2884
2885 if (len == 1 && mod[0] == '=') {
2886
2887 clcf->name = *name;
2888 clcf->exact_match = 1;
2889
2890 } else if (len == 2 && mod[0] == '^' && mod[1] == '~') {
2891
2892 clcf->name = *name;
2893 clcf->noregex = 1;
2894
2895 } else if (len == 1 && mod[0] == '~') {
2896
2897 if (ngx_http_core_regex_location(cf, clcf, name, 0) != NGX_OK) {
2898 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2899 }
2900
2901 } else if (len == 2 && mod[0] == '~' && mod[1] == '*') {
2902
2903 if (ngx_http_core_regex_location(cf, clcf, name, 1) != NGX_OK) {
2904 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2905 }
2906
2907 } else {
2908 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
2909 "invalid location modifier \"%V\"", &value[1]);
2910 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2911 }
2912
2913 } else {
2914
2915 name = &value[1];
2916
2917 if (name->data[0] == '=') {
2918
2919 clcf->name.len = name->len - 1;
2920 clcf->name.data = name->data + 1;
2921 clcf->exact_match = 1;
2922
2923 } else if (name->data[0] == '^' && name->data[1] == '~') {
2924
2925 clcf->name.len = name->len - 2;
2926 clcf->name.data = name->data + 2;
2927 clcf->noregex = 1;
2928
2929 } else if (name->data[0] == '~') {
2930
2931 name->len--;
2932 name->data++;
2933
2934 if (name->data[0] == '*') {
2935
2936 name->len--;
2937 name->data++;
2938
2939 if (ngx_http_core_regex_location(cf, clcf, name, 1) != NGX_OK) {
2940 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2941 }
2942
2943 } else {
2944 if (ngx_http_core_regex_location(cf, clcf, name, 0) != NGX_OK) {
2945 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2946 }
2947 }
2948
2949 } else {
2950
2951 clcf->name = *name;
2952
2953 if (name->data[0] == '@') {
2954 clcf->named = 1;
2955 }
2956 }
2957 }
2958
2959 pclcf = pctx->loc_conf[ngx_http_core_module.ctx_index];
2960
2961 if (cf->cmd_type == NGX_HTTP_LOC_CONF) {
2962
2963 /* nested location */
2964
2965#if 0
2966 clcf->prev_location = pclcf;
2967#endif
2968
2969 if (pclcf->exact_match) {
2970 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
2971 "location \"%V\" cannot be inside "
2972 "the exact location \"%V\"",
2973 &clcf->name, &pclcf->name);
2974 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2975 }
2976
2977 if (pclcf->named) {
2978 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
2979 "location \"%V\" cannot be inside "
2980 "the named location \"%V\"",
2981 &clcf->name, &pclcf->name);
2982 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2983 }
2984
2985 if (clcf->named) {
2986 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
2987 "named location \"%V\" can be "
2988 "on the server level only",
2989 &clcf->name);
2990 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
2991 }
2992
2993 len = pclcf->name.len;
2994
2995#if (NGX_PCRE)
2996 if (clcf->regex == NULL
2997 && ngx_filename_cmp(clcf->name.data, pclcf->name.data, len) != 0)
2998#else
2999 if (ngx_filename_cmp(clcf->name.data, pclcf->name.data, len) != 0)
3000#endif
3001 {
3002 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3003 "location \"%V\" is outside location \"%V\"",
3004 &clcf->name, &pclcf->name);
3005 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3006 }
3007 }
3008
3009 if (ngx_http_add_location(cf, &pclcf->locations, clcf) != NGX_OK) {
3010 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3011 }
3012
3013 save = *cf;
3014 cf->ctx = ctx;
3015 cf->cmd_type = NGX_HTTP_LOC_CONF;
3016
3017 rv = ngx_conf_parse(cf, NULL);
3018
3019 *cf = save;
3020
3021 return rv;
3022}

3025static ngx_int_t
3026ngx_http_core_regex_location(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf,
3027 ngx_str_t *regex, ngx_uint_t caseless)
3028{
3029#if (NGX_PCRE)
3030 ngx_regex_compile_t rc;
3031 u_char errstr[NGX_MAX_CONF_ERRSTR];
3032
3033 ngx_memzero(&rc, sizeof(ngx_regex_compile_t));
3034
3035 rc.pattern = *regex;
3036 rc.err.len = NGX_MAX_CONF_ERRSTR;
3037 rc.err.data = errstr;
3038
3039#if (NGX_HAVE_CASELESS_FILESYSTEM)
3040 rc.options = NGX_REGEX_CASELESS;
3041#else
3042 rc.options = caseless ? NGX_REGEX_CASELESS : 0;
3043#endif
3044
3045 clcf->regex = ngx_http_regex_compile(cf, &rc);
3046 if (clcf->regex == NULL) {
3047 return NGX_ERROR;
3048 }
3049
3050 clcf->name = *regex;
3051
3052 return NGX_OK;
3053
3054#else
3055
3056 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3057 "using regex \"%V\" requires PCRE library",
3058 regex);
3059 return NGX_ERROR;
3060
3061#endif
3062}

3091
3092static char *
3093ngx_http_core_type(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *dummy, void *conf)
3094{
3095 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf = conf;
3096
3097 ngx_str_t *value, *content_type, *old;
3098 ngx_uint_t i, n, hash;
3099 ngx_hash_key_t *type;
3100
3101 value = cf->args->elts;
3102
3103 if (ngx_strcmp(value[0].data, "include") == 0) {
3104 if (cf->args->nelts != 2) {
3105 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3106 "invalid number of arguments"
3107 " in \"include\" directive");
3108 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3109 }
3110
3111 return ngx_conf_include(cf, dummy, conf);
3112 }
3113
3114 content_type = ngx_palloc(cf->pool, sizeof(ngx_str_t));
3115 if (content_type == NULL) {
3116 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3117 }
3118
3119 *content_type = value[0];
3120
3121 for (i = 1; i < cf->args->nelts; i++) {
3122
3123 hash = ngx_hash_strlow(value[i].data, value[i].data, value[i].len);
3124
3125 type = clcf->types->elts;
3126 for (n = 0; n < clcf->types->nelts; n++) {
3127 if (ngx_strcmp(value[i].data, type[n].key.data) == 0) {
3128 old = type[n].value;
3129 type[n].value = content_type;
3130
3131 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_WARN, cf, 0,
3132 "duplicate extension \"%V\", "
3133 "content type: \"%V\", "
3134 "previous content type: \"%V\"",
3135 &value[i], content_type, old);
3136 goto next;
3137 }
3138 }
3139
3140
3141 type = ngx_array_push(clcf->types);
3142 if (type == NULL) {
3143 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3144 }
3145
3146 type->key = value[i];
3147 type->key_hash = hash;
3148 type->value = content_type;
3149
3150 next:
3151 continue;
3152 }
3153
3154 return NGX_CONF_OK;
3155}

3263static char *
3264ngx_http_core_merge_srv_conf(ngx_conf_t *cf, void *parent, void *child)
3265{
3266 ngx_http_core_srv_conf_t *prev = parent;
3267 ngx_http_core_srv_conf_t *conf = child;
3268
3269 ngx_str_t name;
3270 ngx_http_server_name_t *sn;
3271
3272 /* TODO: it does not merge, it inits only */
3273
3274 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->connection_pool_size,
3275 prev->connection_pool_size, 64 * sizeof(void *));
3276 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->request_pool_size,
3277 prev->request_pool_size, 4096);
3278 ngx_conf_merge_msec_value(conf->client_header_timeout,
3279 prev->client_header_timeout, 60000);
3280 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->client_header_buffer_size,
3281 prev->client_header_buffer_size, 1024);
3282 ngx_conf_merge_bufs_value(conf->large_client_header_buffers,
3283 prev->large_client_header_buffers,
3284 4, 8192);
3285
3286 if (conf->large_client_header_buffers.size < conf->connection_pool_size) {
3287 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3288 "the \"large_client_header_buffers\" size must be "
3289 "equal to or greater than \"connection_pool_size\"");
3290 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3291 }
3292
3293 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->ignore_invalid_headers,
3294 prev->ignore_invalid_headers, 1);
3295
3296 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->merge_slashes, prev->merge_slashes, 1);
3297
3298 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->underscores_in_headers,
3299 prev->underscores_in_headers, 0);
3300
3301 if (conf->server_names.nelts == 0) {
3302 /* the array has 4 empty preallocated elements, so push cannot fail */
3303 sn = ngx_array_push(&conf->server_names);
3304#if (NGX_PCRE)
3305 sn->regex = NULL;
3306#endif
3307 sn->server = conf;
3308 ngx_str_set(&sn->name, "");
3309 }
3310
3311 sn = conf->server_names.elts;
3312 name = sn[0].name;
3313
3314#if (NGX_PCRE)
3315 if (sn->regex) {
3316 name.len++;
3317 name.data--;
3318 } else
3319#endif
3320
3321 if (name.data[0] == '.') {
3322 name.len--;
3323 name.data++;
3324 }
3325
3326 conf->server_name.len = name.len;
3327 conf->server_name.data = ngx_pstrdup(cf->pool, &name);
3328 if (conf->server_name.data == NULL) {
3329 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3330 }
3331
3332 return NGX_CONF_OK;
3333}

3454static char *
3455ngx_http_core_merge_loc_conf(ngx_conf_t *cf, void *parent, void *child)
3456{
3457 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *prev = parent;
3458 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *conf = child;
3459
3460 ngx_uint_t i;
3461 ngx_hash_key_t *type;
3462 ngx_hash_init_t types_hash;
3463
3464 if (conf->root.data == NULL) {
3465
3466 conf->alias = prev->alias;
3467 conf->root = prev->root;
3468 conf->root_lengths = prev->root_lengths;
3469 conf->root_values = prev->root_values;
3470
3471 if (prev->root.data == NULL) {
3472 ngx_str_set(&conf->root, "html");
3473
3474 if (ngx_conf_full_name(cf->cycle, &conf->root, 0) != NGX_OK) {
3475 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3476 }
3477 }
3478 }
3479
3480 if (conf->post_action.data == NULL) {
3481 conf->post_action = prev->post_action;
3482 }
3483
3484 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->types_hash_max_size,
3485 prev->types_hash_max_size, 1024);
3486
3487 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->types_hash_bucket_size,
3488 prev->types_hash_bucket_size, 64);

3491 ngx_cacheline_size);
3492
3493 /*
3494 * the special handling of the "types" directive in the "http" section
3495 * to inherit the http's conf->types_hash to all servers
3496 */
3497
3498 if (prev->types && prev->types_hash.buckets == NULL) {
3499
3500 types_hash.hash = &prev->types_hash;
3501 types_hash.key = ngx_hash_key_lc;
3502 types_hash.max_size = conf->types_hash_max_size;
3503 types_hash.bucket_size = conf->types_hash_bucket_size;

3509 != NGX_OK)
3510 {
3511 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3512 }
3513 }
3514
3515 if (conf->types == NULL) {
3516 conf->types = prev->types;
3517 conf->types_hash = prev->types_hash;
3518 }
3519
3520 if (conf->types == NULL) {
3521 conf->types = ngx_array_create(cf->pool, 3, sizeof(ngx_hash_key_t));
3522 if (conf->types == NULL) {
3523 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3524 }
3525
3526 for (i = 0; ngx_http_core_default_types[i].key.len; i++) {
3527 type = ngx_array_push(conf->types);
3528 if (type == NULL) {
3529 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3530 }
3531
3532 type->key = ngx_http_core_default_types[i].key;
3533 type->key_hash =
3534 ngx_hash_key_lc(ngx_http_core_default_types[i].key.data,
3535 ngx_http_core_default_types[i].key.len);
3536 type->value = ngx_http_core_default_types[i].value;
3537 }
3538 }
3539
3540 if (conf->types_hash.buckets == NULL) {
3541
3542 types_hash.hash = &conf->types_hash;
3543 types_hash.key = ngx_hash_key_lc;
3544 types_hash.max_size = conf->types_hash_max_size;
3545 types_hash.bucket_size = conf->types_hash_bucket_size;
3546 types_hash.name = "types_hash";
3547 types_hash.pool = cf->pool;
3548 types_hash.temp_pool = NULL;
3549
3550 if (ngx_hash_init(&types_hash, conf->types->elts, conf->types->nelts)
3551 != NGX_OK)
3552 {
3553 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3554 }
3555 }
3556
3557 if (conf->error_log == NULL) {
3558 if (prev->error_log) {
3559 conf->error_log = prev->error_log;
3560 } else {
3561 conf->error_log = &cf->cycle->new_log;
3562 }
3563 }
3564
3565 if (conf->error_pages == NULL && prev->error_pages) {
3566 conf->error_pages = prev->error_pages;
3567 }
3568
3569 ngx_conf_merge_str_value(conf->default_type,
3570 prev->default_type, "text/plain");
3571
3572 ngx_conf_merge_off_value(conf->client_max_body_size,
3573 prev->client_max_body_size, 1 * 1024 * 1024);
3574 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->client_body_buffer_size,
3575 prev->client_body_buffer_size,
3576 (size_t) 2 * ngx_pagesize);
3577 ngx_conf_merge_msec_value(conf->client_body_timeout,
3578 prev->client_body_timeout, 60000);
3579
3580 ngx_conf_merge_bitmask_value(conf->keepalive_disable,
3581 prev->keepalive_disable,
3582 (NGX_CONF_BITMASK_SET
3583 |NGX_HTTP_KEEPALIVE_DISABLE_MSIE6));
3584 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->satisfy, prev->satisfy,
3585 NGX_HTTP_SATISFY_ALL);
3586 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->if_modified_since, prev->if_modified_since,
3587 NGX_HTTP_IMS_EXACT);
3588 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->max_ranges, prev->max_ranges,
3589 NGX_MAX_INT32_VALUE);
3590 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->client_body_in_file_only,
3591 prev->client_body_in_file_only,
3592 NGX_HTTP_REQUEST_BODY_FILE_OFF);
3593 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->client_body_in_single_buffer,
3594 prev->client_body_in_single_buffer, 0);
3595 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->internal, prev->internal, 0);
3596 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->sendfile, prev->sendfile, 0);
3597 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->sendfile_max_chunk,
3598 prev->sendfile_max_chunk, 0);
3599 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->subrequest_output_buffer_size,
3600 prev->subrequest_output_buffer_size,
3601 (size_t) ngx_pagesize);
3602 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->aio, prev->aio, NGX_HTTP_AIO_OFF);
3603 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->aio_write, prev->aio_write, 0);
3604#if (NGX_THREADS)
3605 ngx_conf_merge_ptr_value(conf->thread_pool, prev->thread_pool, NULL);
3606 ngx_conf_merge_ptr_value(conf->thread_pool_value, prev->thread_pool_value,
3607 NULL);
3608#endif
3609 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->read_ahead, prev->read_ahead, 0);
3610 ngx_conf_merge_off_value(conf->directio, prev->directio,
3611 NGX_OPEN_FILE_DIRECTIO_OFF);
3612 ngx_conf_merge_off_value(conf->directio_alignment, prev->directio_alignment,
3613 512);
3614 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->tcp_nopush, prev->tcp_nopush, 0);
3615 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->tcp_nodelay, prev->tcp_nodelay, 1);
3616
3617 ngx_conf_merge_msec_value(conf->send_timeout, prev->send_timeout, 60000);

3620 1460);
3621 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->limit_rate, prev->limit_rate, 0);
3622 ngx_conf_merge_size_value(conf->limit_rate_after, prev->limit_rate_after,
3623 0);
3624 ngx_conf_merge_msec_value(conf->keepalive_timeout,
3625 prev->keepalive_timeout, 75000);
3626 ngx_conf_merge_sec_value(conf->keepalive_header,
3627 prev->keepalive_header, 0);
3628 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->keepalive_requests,
3629 prev->keepalive_requests, 100);
3630 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->lingering_close,
3631 prev->lingering_close, NGX_HTTP_LINGERING_ON);
3632 ngx_conf_merge_msec_value(conf->lingering_time,
3633 prev->lingering_time, 30000);
3634 ngx_conf_merge_msec_value(conf->lingering_timeout,
3635 prev->lingering_timeout, 5000);
3636 ngx_conf_merge_msec_value(conf->resolver_timeout,
3637 prev->resolver_timeout, 30000);
3638
3639 if (conf->resolver == NULL) {
3640
3641 if (prev->resolver == NULL) {
3642
3643 /*
3644 * create dummy resolver in http {} context
3645 * to inherit it in all servers
3646 */
3647
3648 prev->resolver = ngx_resolver_create(cf, NULL, 0);
3649 if (prev->resolver == NULL) {
3650 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3651 }
3652 }
3653
3654 conf->resolver = prev->resolver;
3655 }
3656
3657 if (ngx_conf_merge_path_value(cf, &conf->client_body_temp_path,
3658 prev->client_body_temp_path,
3659 &ngx_http_client_temp_path)
3660 != NGX_OK)
3661 {
3662 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3663 }
3664
3665 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->reset_timedout_connection,
3666 prev->reset_timedout_connection, 0);
3667 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->absolute_redirect,
3668 prev->absolute_redirect, 1);
3669 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->server_name_in_redirect,
3670 prev->server_name_in_redirect, 0);
3671 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->port_in_redirect, prev->port_in_redirect, 1);
3672 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->msie_padding, prev->msie_padding, 1);
3673 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->msie_refresh, prev->msie_refresh, 0);
3674 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->log_not_found, prev->log_not_found, 1);
3675 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->log_subrequest, prev->log_subrequest, 0);
3676 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->recursive_error_pages,
3677 prev->recursive_error_pages, 0);
3678 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->chunked_transfer_encoding,
3679 prev->chunked_transfer_encoding, 1);
3680 ngx_conf_merge_value(conf->etag, prev->etag, 1);
3681
3682 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->server_tokens, prev->server_tokens,
3683 NGX_HTTP_SERVER_TOKENS_ON);
3684
3685 ngx_conf_merge_ptr_value(conf->open_file_cache,
3686 prev->open_file_cache, NULL);
3687
3688 ngx_conf_merge_sec_value(conf->open_file_cache_valid,
3689 prev->open_file_cache_valid, 60);
3690
3691 ngx_conf_merge_uint_value(conf->open_file_cache_min_uses,
3692 prev->open_file_cache_min_uses, 1);
3693
3694 ngx_conf_merge_sec_value(conf->open_file_cache_errors,
3695 prev->open_file_cache_errors, 0);

3700

3732#endif

3737
3738static char *
3739ngx_http_core_listen(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *conf)
3740{
3741 ngx_http_core_srv_conf_t *cscf = conf;
3742
3743 ngx_str_t *value, size;
3744 ngx_url_t u;
3745 ngx_uint_t n;
3746 ngx_http_listen_opt_t lsopt;
3747
3748 cscf->listen = 1;
3749
3750 value = cf->args->elts;
3751
3752 ngx_memzero(&u, sizeof(ngx_url_t));
3753
3754 u.url = value[1];
3755 u.listen = 1;
3756 u.default_port = 80;
3757
3758 if (ngx_parse_url(cf->pool, &u) != NGX_OK) {
3759 if (u.err) {
3760 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3761 "%s in \"%V\" of the \"listen\" directive",
3762 u.err, &u.url);
3763 }
3764
3765 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3766 }
3767
3768 ngx_memzero(&lsopt, sizeof(ngx_http_listen_opt_t));
3769
3770 ngx_memcpy(&lsopt.sockaddr.sockaddr, &u.sockaddr, u.socklen);
3771
3772 lsopt.socklen = u.socklen;
3773 lsopt.backlog = NGX_LISTEN_BACKLOG;
3774 lsopt.rcvbuf = -1;
3775 lsopt.sndbuf = -1;
3776#if (NGX_HAVE_SETFIB)
3777 lsopt.setfib = -1;
3778#endif
3779#if (NGX_HAVE_TCP_FASTOPEN)
3780 lsopt.fastopen = -1;
3781#endif
3782 lsopt.wildcard = u.wildcard;
3783#if (NGX_HAVE_INET6)
3784 lsopt.ipv6only = 1;
3785#endif
3786
3787 (void) ngx_sock_ntop(&lsopt.sockaddr.sockaddr, lsopt.socklen, lsopt.addr,
3788 NGX_SOCKADDR_STRLEN, 1);
3789
3790 for (n = 2; n < cf->args->nelts; n++) {
3791
3792 if (ngx_strcmp(value[n].data, "default_server") == 0
3793 || ngx_strcmp(value[n].data, "default") == 0)
3794 {
3795 lsopt.default_server = 1;
3796 continue;
3797 }
3798
3799 if (ngx_strcmp(value[n].data, "bind") == 0) {
3800 lsopt.set = 1;
3801 lsopt.bind = 1;
3802 continue;
3803 }
3804
3805#if (NGX_HAVE_SETFIB)
3806 if (ngx_strncmp(value[n].data, "setfib=", 7) == 0) {
3807 lsopt.setfib = ngx_atoi(value[n].data + 7, value[n].len - 7);
3808 lsopt.set = 1;
3809 lsopt.bind = 1;
3810
3811 if (lsopt.setfib == NGX_ERROR) {
3812 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3813 "invalid setfib \"%V\"", &value[n]);
3814 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3815 }
3816
3817 continue;
3818 }
3819#endif
3820
3821#if (NGX_HAVE_TCP_FASTOPEN)
3822 if (ngx_strncmp(value[n].data, "fastopen=", 9) == 0) {
3823 lsopt.fastopen = ngx_atoi(value[n].data + 9, value[n].len - 9);
3824 lsopt.set = 1;
3825 lsopt.bind = 1;
3826
3827 if (lsopt.fastopen == NGX_ERROR) {
3828 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3829 "invalid fastopen \"%V\"", &value[n]);
3830 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3831 }
3832
3833 continue;
3834 }
3835#endif
3836
3837 if (ngx_strncmp(value[n].data, "backlog=", 8) == 0) {
3838 lsopt.backlog = ngx_atoi(value[n].data + 8, value[n].len - 8);
3839 lsopt.set = 1;
3840 lsopt.bind = 1;
3841
3842 if (lsopt.backlog == NGX_ERROR || lsopt.backlog == 0) {
3843 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
3844 "invalid backlog \"%V\"", &value[n]);
3845 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
3846 }
3847
3848 continue;
3849 }
3850
3851 if (ngx_strncmp(value[n].data, "rcvbuf=", 7) == 0) {
3852 size.len = value[n].len - 7;
3853 size.data = value[n].data + 7;
3854
3855 lsopt.rcvbuf = ngx_parse_size(&size);
3856 lsopt.set = 1;
3857 lsopt.bind = 1;
3858
3859 if (lsopt.rcvbuf == NGX_ERROR) {
3860 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,

3889 lsopt.bind = 1;

3894 &value[n]);

3900#if (NGX_HAVE_DEFERRED_ACCEPT && defined TCP_DEFER_ACCEPT)

3970 "the \"ssl\" parameter requires "
3971 "ngx_http_ssl_module");

3973#endif

3976 if (ngx_strcmp(value[n].data, "http2") == 0) {
3977#if (NGX_HTTP_V2)
3978 lsopt.http2 = 1;

3980#else

3985#endif

3990 "invalid parameter \"spdy\": "
3991 "ngx_http_spdy_module was superseded "

3997

3999 lsopt.so_keepalive = 1;
4000
4001 } else if (ngx_strcmp(&value[n].data[13], "off") == 0) {
4002 lsopt.so_keepalive = 2;
4003
4004 } else {
4005
4006#if (NGX_HAVE_KEEPALIVE_TUNABLE)
4007 u_char *p, *end;
4008 ngx_str_t s;
4009
4010 end = value[n].data + value[n].len;
4011 s.data = value[n].data + 13;
4012
4013 p = ngx_strlchr(s.data, end, ':');
4014 if (p == NULL) {
4015 p = end;
4016 }
4017
4018 if (p > s.data) {
4019 s.len = p - s.data;
4020
4021 lsopt.tcp_keepidle = ngx_parse_time(&s, 1);
4022 if (lsopt.tcp_keepidle == (time_t) NGX_ERROR) {
4023 goto invalid_so_keepalive;
4024 }
4025 }
4026
4027 s.data = (p < end) ? (p + 1) : end;
4028
4029 p = ngx_strlchr(s.data, end, ':');
4030 if (p == NULL) {
4031 p = end;
4032 }
4033
4034 if (p > s.data) {
4035 s.len = p - s.data;
4036
4037 lsopt.tcp_keepintvl = ngx_parse_time(&s, 1);
4038 if (lsopt.tcp_keepintvl == (time_t) NGX_ERROR) {
4039 goto invalid_so_keepalive;
4040 }
4041 }
4042
4043 s.data = (p < end) ? (p + 1) : end;
4044
4045 if (s.data < end) {
4046 s.len = end - s.data;
4047
4048 lsopt.tcp_keepcnt = ngx_atoi(s.data, s.len);
4049 if (lsopt.tcp_keepcnt == NGX_ERROR) {
4050 goto invalid_so_keepalive;
4051 }
4052 }
4053
4054 if (lsopt.tcp_keepidle == 0 && lsopt.tcp_keepintvl == 0
4055 && lsopt.tcp_keepcnt == 0)
4056 {
4057 goto invalid_so_keepalive;
4058 }
4059
4060 lsopt.so_keepalive = 1;
4061
4062#else
4063
4064 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4065 "the \"so_keepalive\" parameter accepts "
4066 "only \"on\" or \"off\" on this platform");
4067 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4068
4069#endif
4070 }
4071
4072 lsopt.set = 1;
4073 lsopt.bind = 1;
4074
4075 continue;
4076
4077#if (NGX_HAVE_KEEPALIVE_TUNABLE)
4078 invalid_so_keepalive:
4079
4080 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4081 "invalid so_keepalive value: \"%s\"",
4082 &value[n].data[13]);
4083 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4084#endif
4085 }
4086
4087 if (ngx_strcmp(value[n].data, "proxy_protocol") == 0) {
4088 lsopt.proxy_protocol = 1;
4089 continue;
4090 }
4091
4092 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4093 "invalid parameter \"%V\"", &value[n]);
4094 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4095 }
4096
4097 if (ngx_http_add_listen(cf, cscf, &lsopt) == NGX_OK) {
4098 return NGX_CONF_OK;
4099 }
4100
4101 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4102}

4104
4105static char *
4106ngx_http_core_server_name(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *conf)
4107{
4108 ngx_http_core_srv_conf_t *cscf = conf;
4109
4110 u_char ch;
4111 ngx_str_t *value;
4112 ngx_uint_t i;
4113 ngx_http_server_name_t *sn;
4114
4115 value = cf->args->elts;
4116
4117 for (i = 1; i < cf->args->nelts; i++) {
4118
4119 ch = value[i].data[0];
4120
4121 if ((ch == '*' && (value[i].len < 3 || value[i].data[1] != '.'))
4122 || (ch == '.' && value[i].len < 2))
4123 {
4124 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4125 "server name \"%V\" is invalid", &value[i]);
4126 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4127 }
4128
4129 if (ngx_strchr(value[i].data, '/')) {
4130 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_WARN, cf, 0,
4131 "server name \"%V\" has suspicious symbols",
4132 &value[i]);
4133 }
4134
4135 sn = ngx_array_push(&cscf->server_names);
4136 if (sn == NULL) {
4137 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4138 }
4139
4140#if (NGX_PCRE)
4141 sn->regex = NULL;
4142#endif
4143 sn->server = cscf;
4144
4145 if (ngx_strcasecmp(value[i].data, (u_char *) "$hostname") == 0) {
4146 sn->name = cf->cycle->hostname;
4147
4148 } else {
4149 sn->name = value[i];
4150 }
4151
4152 if (value[i].data[0] != '~') {
4153 ngx_strlow(sn->name.data, sn->name.data, sn->name.len);
4154 continue;
4155 }
4156
4157#if (NGX_PCRE)
4158 {
4159 u_char *p;
4160 ngx_regex_compile_t rc;
4161 u_char errstr[NGX_MAX_CONF_ERRSTR];
4162
4163 if (value[i].len == 1) {
4164 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4165 "empty regex in server name \"%V\"", &value[i]);
4166 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4167 }
4168
4169 value[i].len--;
4170 value[i].data++;
4171
4172 ngx_memzero(&rc, sizeof(ngx_regex_compile_t));
4173
4174 rc.pattern = value[i];
4175 rc.err.len = NGX_MAX_CONF_ERRSTR;
4176 rc.err.data = errstr;
4177
4178 for (p = value[i].data; p < value[i].data + value[i].len; p++) {
4179 if (*p >= 'A' && *p <= 'Z') {
4180 rc.options = NGX_REGEX_CASELESS;
4181 break;
4182 }
4183 }
4184
4185 sn->regex = ngx_http_regex_compile(cf, &rc);
4186 if (sn->regex == NULL) {
4187 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4188 }
4189
4190 sn->name = value[i];
4191 cscf->captures = (rc.captures > 0);
4192 }
4193#else
4194 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4195 "using regex \"%V\" "
4196 "requires PCRE library", &value[i]);
4197
4198 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4199#endif
4200 }
4201
4202 return NGX_CONF_OK;
4203}

4206static char *
4207ngx_http_core_root(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *conf)
4208{
4209 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf = conf;
4210
4211 ngx_str_t *value;
4212 ngx_int_t alias;
4213 ngx_uint_t n;
4214 ngx_http_script_compile_t sc;
4215
4216 alias = (cmd->name.len == sizeof("alias") - 1) ? 1 : 0;
4217
4218 if (clcf->root.data) {
4219
4220 if ((clcf->alias != 0) == alias) {
4221 return "is duplicate";
4222 }
4223
4224 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4225 "\"%V\" directive is duplicate, "
4226 "\"%s\" directive was specified earlier",
4227 &cmd->name, clcf->alias ? "alias" : "root");
4228
4229 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4230 }
4231
4232 if (clcf->named && alias) {
4233 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4234 "the \"alias\" directive cannot be used "
4235 "inside the named location");
4236
4237 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4238 }
4239
4240 value = cf->args->elts;
4241
4242 if (ngx_strstr(value[1].data, "$document_root")
4243 || ngx_strstr(value[1].data, "${document_root}"))
4244 {
4245 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4246 "the $document_root variable cannot be used "
4247 "in the \"%V\" directive",
4248 &cmd->name);
4249
4250 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4251 }
4252
4253 if (ngx_strstr(value[1].data, "$realpath_root")
4254 || ngx_strstr(value[1].data, "${realpath_root}"))
4255 {
4256 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4257 "the $realpath_root variable cannot be used "
4258 "in the \"%V\" directive",
4259 &cmd->name);
4260
4261 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4262 }
4263
4264 clcf->alias = alias ? clcf->name.len : 0;
4265 clcf->root = value[1];
4266
4267 if (!alias && clcf->root.len > 0
4268 && clcf->root.data[clcf->root.len - 1] == '/')
4269 {
4270 clcf->root.len--;
4271 }
4272
4273 if (clcf->root.data[0] != '$') {
4274 if (ngx_conf_full_name(cf->cycle, &clcf->root, 0) != NGX_OK) {
4275 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4276 }
4277 }
4278
4279 n = ngx_http_script_variables_count(&clcf->root);
4280
4281 ngx_memzero(&sc, sizeof(ngx_http_script_compile_t));
4282 sc.variables = n;
4283
4284#if (NGX_PCRE)
4285 if (alias && clcf->regex) {
4286 clcf->alias = NGX_MAX_SIZE_T_VALUE;
4287 n = 1;
4288 }
4289#endif
4290
4291 if (n) {
4292 sc.cf = cf;
4293 sc.source = &clcf->root;
4294 sc.lengths = &clcf->root_lengths;
4295 sc.values = &clcf->root_values;
4296 sc.complete_lengths = 1;
4297 sc.complete_values = 1;
4298
4299 if (ngx_http_script_compile(&sc) != NGX_OK) {
4300 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4301 }
4302 }
4303
4304 return NGX_CONF_OK;
4305}

4327static char *
4328ngx_http_core_limit_except(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *conf)
4329{
4330 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *pclcf = conf;
4331
4332 char *rv;
4333 void *mconf;
4334 ngx_str_t *value;
4335 ngx_uint_t i;
4336 ngx_conf_t save;
4337 ngx_http_module_t *module;
4338 ngx_http_conf_ctx_t *ctx, *pctx;
4339 ngx_http_method_name_t *name;
4340 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf;
4341
4342 if (pclcf->limit_except) {
4343 return "is duplicate";
4344 }
4345
4346 pclcf->limit_except = 0xffffffff;
4347
4348 value = cf->args->elts;
4349
4350 for (i = 1; i < cf->args->nelts; i++) {
4351 for (name = ngx_methods_names; name->name; name++) {
4352
4353 if (ngx_strcasecmp(value[i].data, name->name) == 0) {
4354 pclcf->limit_except &= name->method;
4355 goto next;
4356 }
4357 }
4358
4359 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4360 "invalid method \"%V\"", &value[i]);
4361 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4362
4363 next:
4364 continue;
4365 }
4366
4367 if (!(pclcf->limit_except & NGX_HTTP_GET)) {
4368 pclcf->limit_except &= (uint32_t) ~NGX_HTTP_HEAD;
4369 }
4370
4371 ctx = ngx_pcalloc(cf->pool, sizeof(ngx_http_conf_ctx_t));
4372 if (ctx == NULL) {
4373 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4374 }
4375
4376 pctx = cf->ctx;
4377 ctx->main_conf = pctx->main_conf;
4378 ctx->srv_conf = pctx->srv_conf;
4379
4380 ctx->loc_conf = ngx_pcalloc(cf->pool, sizeof(void *) * ngx_http_max_module);
4381 if (ctx->loc_conf == NULL) {
4382 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4383 }
4384
4385 for (i = 0; cf->cycle->modules[i]; i++) {
4386 if (cf->cycle->modules[i]->type != NGX_HTTP_MODULE) {
4387 continue;
4388 }
4389
4390 module = cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx;
4391
4392 if (module->create_loc_conf) {
4393
4394 mconf = module->create_loc_conf(cf);
4395 if (mconf == NULL) {
4396 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4397 }
4398
4399 ctx->loc_conf[cf->cycle->modules[i]->ctx_index] = mconf;
4400 }
4401 }
4402
4403
4404 clcf = ctx->loc_conf[ngx_http_core_module.ctx_index];
4405 pclcf->limit_except_loc_conf = ctx->loc_conf;
4406 clcf->loc_conf = ctx->loc_conf;
4407 clcf->name = pclcf->name;
4408 clcf->noname = 1;
4409 clcf->lmt_excpt = 1;
4410
4411 if (ngx_http_add_location(cf, &pclcf->locations, clcf) != NGX_OK) {
4412 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4413 }
4414
4415 save = *cf;
4416 cf->ctx = ctx;
4417 cf->cmd_type = NGX_HTTP_LMT_CONF;
4418
4419 rv = ngx_conf_parse(cf, NULL);
4420
4421 *cf = save;
4422
4423 return rv;
4424}

4564static char *
4565ngx_http_core_error_page(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *conf)
4566{
4567 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf = conf;
4568
4569 u_char *p;
4570 ngx_int_t overwrite;
4571 ngx_str_t *value, uri, args;
4572 ngx_uint_t i, n;
4573 ngx_http_err_page_t *err;
4574 ngx_http_complex_value_t cv;
4575 ngx_http_compile_complex_value_t ccv;
4576
4577 if (clcf->error_pages == NULL) {
4578 clcf->error_pages = ngx_array_create(cf->pool, 4,
4579 sizeof(ngx_http_err_page_t));
4580 if (clcf->error_pages == NULL) {
4581 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4582 }
4583 }
4584
4585 value = cf->args->elts;
4586
4587 i = cf->args->nelts - 2;
4588
4589 if (value[i].data[0] == '=') {
4590 if (i == 1) {
4591 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4592 "invalid value \"%V\"", &value[i]);
4593 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4594 }
4595
4596 if (value[i].len > 1) {
4597 overwrite = ngx_atoi(&value[i].data[1], value[i].len - 1);
4598
4599 if (overwrite == NGX_ERROR) {
4600 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4601 "invalid value \"%V\"", &value[i]);
4602 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4603 }
4604
4605 } else {
4606 overwrite = 0;
4607 }
4608
4609 n = 2;
4610
4611 } else {
4612 overwrite = -1;
4613 n = 1;
4614 }
4615
4616 uri = value[cf->args->nelts - 1];
4617
4618 ngx_memzero(&ccv, sizeof(ngx_http_compile_complex_value_t));
4619
4620 ccv.cf = cf;
4621 ccv.value = &uri;
4622 ccv.complex_value = &cv;
4623
4624 if (ngx_http_compile_complex_value(&ccv) != NGX_OK) {
4625 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4626 }
4627
4628 ngx_str_null(&args);
4629
4630 if (cv.lengths == NULL && uri.len && uri.data[0] == '/') {
4631 p = (u_char *) ngx_strchr(uri.data, '?');
4632
4633 if (p) {
4634 cv.value.len = p - uri.data;
4635 cv.value.data = uri.data;
4636 p++;
4637 args.len = (uri.data + uri.len) - p;
4638 args.data = p;
4639 }
4640 }
4641
4642 for (i = 1; i < cf->args->nelts - n; i++) {
4643 err = ngx_array_push(clcf->error_pages);
4644 if (err == NULL) {
4645 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4646 }
4647
4648 err->status = ngx_atoi(value[i].data, value[i].len);
4649
4650 if (err->status == NGX_ERROR || err->status == 499) {
4651 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4652 "invalid value \"%V\"", &value[i]);
4653 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4654 }
4655
4656 if (err->status < 300 || err->status > 599) {
4657 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4658 "value \"%V\" must be between 300 and 599",
4659 &value[i]);
4660 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4661 }
4662
4663 err->overwrite = overwrite;
4664
4665 if (overwrite == -1) {
4666 switch (err->status) {
4667 case NGX_HTTP_TO_HTTPS:
4668 case NGX_HTTPS_CERT_ERROR:
4669 case NGX_HTTPS_NO_CERT:
4670 err->overwrite = NGX_HTTP_BAD_REQUEST;
4671 }
4672 }
4673
4674 err->value = cv;
4675 err->args = args;
4676 }
4677
4678 return NGX_CONF_OK;
4679}

4682static char *
4683ngx_http_core_open_file_cache(ngx_conf_t *cf, ngx_command_t *cmd, void *conf)
4684{
4685 ngx_http_core_loc_conf_t *clcf = conf;
4686
4687 time_t inactive;
4688 ngx_str_t *value, s;
4689 ngx_int_t max;
4690 ngx_uint_t i;
4691
4692 if (clcf->open_file_cache != NGX_CONF_UNSET_PTR) {
4693 return "is duplicate";
4694 }
4695
4696 value = cf->args->elts;
4697
4698 max = 0;
4699 inactive = 60;
4700
4701 for (i = 1; i < cf->args->nelts; i++) {
4702
4703 if (ngx_strncmp(value[i].data, "max=", 4) == 0) {
4704
4705 max = ngx_atoi(value[i].data + 4, value[i].len - 4);
4706 if (max <= 0) {
4707 goto failed;
4708 }
4709
4710 continue;
4711 }
4712
4713 if (ngx_strncmp(value[i].data, "inactive=", 9) == 0) {
4714
4715 s.len = value[i].len - 9;
4716 s.data = value[i].data + 9;
4717
4718 inactive = ngx_parse_time(&s, 1);
4719 if (inactive == (time_t) NGX_ERROR) {
4720 goto failed;
4721 }
4722
4723 continue;
4724 }
4725
4726 if (ngx_strcmp(value[i].data, "off") == 0) {
4727
4728 clcf->open_file_cache = NULL;
4729
4730 continue;
4731 }
4732
4733 failed:
4734
4735 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4736 "invalid \"open_file_cache\" parameter \"%V\"",
4737 &value[i]);
4738 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4739 }
4740
4741 if (clcf->open_file_cache == NULL) {
4742 return NGX_CONF_OK;
4743 }
4744
4745 if (max == 0) {
4746 ngx_conf_log_error(NGX_LOG_EMERG, cf, 0,
4747 "\"open_file_cache\" must have the \"max\" parameter");
4748 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4749 }
4750
4751 clcf->open_file_cache = ngx_open_file_cache_init(cf->pool, max, inactive);
4752 if (clcf->open_file_cache) {
4753 return NGX_CONF_OK;
4754 }
4755
4756 return NGX_CONF_ERROR;
4757}
